{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nProvision the auto-lander bot's Gerrit credential and the access right it needs to rebase changes on behalf of their uploader ‚Äî reusing the project's existing ACL machinery, without a redundant grant or an IAM change. Split out of S5 (`perpetual-ultrasonic-raccoon`).\n\n## Files\n- `infra/terraform/ssm.tf` ‚Äî EDIT: add `/rebar/prod/autolander-gerrit-token` to the existing `local.rebar_secret_params` set (the `for_each` `aws_ssm_parameter` resource with `ignore_changes = [value]` + CHANGEME sentinel), NOT a standalone resource.\n- `infra/scripts/fetch-secrets.sh` ‚Äî EDIT: add the mapping `autolander-gerrit-token ‚Üí AUTOLANDER_GERRIT_TOKEN`, materialized into the SAME shared `.env` (distinct env-var from the review-bot's `GERRIT_BOT_TOKEN`).\n- `infra/gerrit/project.config` + `infra/gerrit/setup-project.sh` ‚Äî EDIT: grant the bot the **Rebase** access right (and the rebase-on-behalf-of-uploader form) on the `rebar` project's `refs/heads/*`. This lives in the **rebar project's own** `refs/meta/config` (managed here), NOT `All-Projects`.\n- `infra/gerrit/smoke-check-autolander.sh` ‚Äî NEW: the autolander live smoke test (the existing `smoke-check.sh` covers only the review-bot; the autolander steps are distinct).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] **Credential:** the Gerrit HTTP token is an SSM **SecureString** at `/rebar/prod/autolander-gerrit-token` ‚Äî inside the existing `parameter/rebar/prod/*` prefix the EC2 instance-role IAM policy (`iam.tf` `ssm_params_read`) already grants, so **NO IAM change** (`iam.tf` read-only/unchanged; a `/rebar/autolander/*` path would fall outside the grant). Added via the `ssm.tf` `for_each` set; fetched by `fetch-secrets.sh` using **`get_param` (required/fail-fast ‚Äî NOT `get_param_optional`)** so a missing token aborts boot rather than silently producing a blank env-var, into the shared `.env` as `AUTOLANDER_GERRIT_TOKEN`; never inlined.\n- [ ] **Submit is already covered ‚Äî do NOT add a submit grant.** `RebarBotNava` is already in the `Contributors` group (`setup-project.sh` default `CONTRIBUTOR_MEMBERS`), which holds `Submit` on `refs/heads/*`. An All-Projects submit grant would be **eclipsed** anyway: `project.config` sets `exclusiveGroupPermissions = submit`, so Gerrit ignores inherited submit for that ref. AC = *verify* `RebarBotNava ‚àà Contributors` (so `POST /submit` does not 403); no new submit ACL.\n- [ ] **Rebase-on-behalf access right (concrete):** grant the **`Rebase`** access right (project.config `[access]` token **`rebase`**, confirmed in this instance's `access-control.html`) to group **`Contributors`** on the `rebar` project's `refs/heads/*` ‚Äî added to the **rebar project's** `refs/meta/config` via `setup-project.sh`/`project.config` (NOT `All-Projects`, NOT a global `[capability]`, NOT the `[submit] rebaseOnBehalfOfUploader` submit-strategy setting). Concrete stanza: `[access \"refs/heads/*\"] rebase = group Contributors`. The **on-behalf** half needs no extra grant: `rebase_on_behalf_of_uploader` checks push/upload against the *original uploader*, who already holds it (they created the change). (The bot is already a submitter via Contributors, and \"submitters can always rebase\" per the ACL docs, so this explicit `rebase` grant is belt-and-suspenders for the REST path.)\n- [ ] **Fallback protocol (no silent failure):** the AC3 smoke test is the checkpoint ‚Äî if the live rebase-on-behalf call 403s despite the `rebase` grant, the 403 body names the missing right; the documented remediation is to add exactly that named right to the same `refs/heads/*` stanza. The plan does NOT proceed to production on a 403.\n- [ ] **Tests (AC3):** `setup-project.sh` remains idempotent (re-run is a no-op). `infra/gerrit/smoke-check-autolander.sh` runs against the live instance, all on an **isolated scratch branch** so it never touches real work: (1) ensure a dedicated `refs/heads/scratch-autolander` branch exists (create if absent ‚Äî idempotent); (2) confirm the token materialized into `.env` and `RebarBotNava` authenticates; (3) push a synthetic change to `refs/for/scratch-autolander` (uploaded as a distinct throwaway identity so \"uploader preserved\" is observable); (4) rebase-on-behalf via the REST API and **assert the uploader is preserved with a concrete command** ‚Äî `curl -s -u \"$CRED\" \".../a/changes/{id}/detail?o=CURRENT_REVISION\" | jq -r '.revisions[.current_revision].uploader.username'` equals the original uploader, NOT `RebarBotNava`; (5) submit it ‚Äî it merges into the **isolated `scratch-autolander` branch** (harmless, no real branch touched), so NO post-merge abandon is needed (a merged change cannot be abandoned); (6) cleanup resets/prunes the scratch branch. On a 403 at step 4, the fallback protocol above applies."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783841936538703001,"uuid":"2c018dd6-02ae-485b-acda-186012e5caa7"}